    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but i've been reading some stuff online saying that originalism is basically just a way for judges to push a conservative agenda by ignoring modern social standards. how would an originalist respond to the critique that their method is basically just \"lawmaking\" disguised as history?",
